      <h3>Make Changes on a Forked Repository ğŸ”„</h3>
      <p>
        Clone your forked repository, make a small edit, and push it back to GitHub.
        <strong>Goal:</strong> Practice making contributions to projects you donâ€™t own.
      </p>
      
      <h3>Submit a Pull Request to the Original Repository ğŸ“¨</h3>
      <p>
        From your fork, open a PR to the original repo with your edits.
